Dr. '''Catherine Ball''' is a businesswoman with a focus on environmental science and technology. Ball is currently operating a number of start up companies. <ref>https://www.telstrabusinesswomensawards.com/news/2015/drone-pioneer-named-queenslands-top-business-woman/</ref> She is renowned for her work with drone technology advancement which has been a main source for her recent recognition. Ball and her team operated a drone that could fly hundreds of kilometers. They flew it off the west coast of Australia to study and track turtle habitats. During this 'same voyage' they found endangered animals that had not been seen for years.<ref>http://www.smh.com.au/business/telstra-queensland-business-woman-of-year-catherine-ball-wins-for-drone-work-20150929-gjxoai.html</ref> This thought leadership is what landed her the 2015 Telestra Queensland Business Woman of the Year award.<ref>http://www.smh.com.au/business/telstra-queensland-business-woman-of-year-catherine-ball-wins-for-drone-work-20150929-gjxoai.html</ref> Ball identifies as a representative for women in [[Science, technology, engineering, and mathematics|STEM]].<ref>https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine</ref> She has degrees in environmental protection, ecology, and statistics and is a businesswoman making advancements in the technological field to help with environmental protection.<ref>https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine</ref>

== Personal ==
Ball was born in UK, England, however considers herself an Aussie-at-heart, due to the 'amount of work' she has done in Australia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spatialsource.com.au/latest-news/position-qa-with-dr-catherine-ball|title=Position Q&A with Dr Catherine Ball|date=2016-03-09|newspaper=Spatial Source|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref> At a young age, Ball had a wide exposure to different cultures and experiences, due to traveling for school. At the age of 13 she attended school in France and at the age of 18 in Zambia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine|title=Dr Catherine Ball--Managing Director|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref> Ball attributes her diverse career choices to these experiences and opportunities she had growing up.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine|title=Dr Catherine Ball--Managing Director|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref> At the age of 30 she moved to Australia all by herself. What encouraged Ball to take this next step in her life was her strong belief in the phrase "feeling the fear and doing it anyways".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine|title=Dr Catherine Ball--Managing Director|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref>

== Education ==

Catherine Ball first attended [http://www.highamlaneschool.co.uk/news/?pid=3&nid=1&storyid=423 Higham Lane] where she received her [[General Certificate of Secondary Education|GCSE]]<nowiki/>s from 1991 through 1995. Then she later went on to [[King Edward VI College, Stourbridge#A-Level .26 AS Subjects|King Edward VI College]] where she had her A Levels in Biology, Chemistry, Physics and French.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/catherinemarieball?authType=name&authToken=EHm6|title=LinkedIn|last=Ball|first=Catherine|date=|website=|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Ball received her Bachelors in Science with honors in Environmental Protection at the [[University of Newcastle upon Tyne]] in 1998 through 2002.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/catherinemarieball?authType=name&authToken=EHm6|title=LinkedIn|last=Ball|first=Catherine|date=|website=|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> She went on to complete her Ph.D in Ecology and Statistics at the same university in 2008; while also studying Microbial Ecology, Molecular Biology, Statistics and Modeling.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/catherinemarieball?authType=name&authToken=EHm6|title=LinkedIn|last=Ball|first=Catherine|date=|website=|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

.<ref>https://www.elemental-strategy.com/index.php/thought-leaders/catherine</ref>

== Awards ==
Ball was recognized with the 2015 Telstra Queensland Business Woman of the Year award. She was also on the Q Magazine's "2015 Queensland 50 Best and Bright" list. She was on the Australian Financial Review BOSS Magazine's "2015 Young Executives of the Year."

