'''Léon Lhoist''' was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. In 1889 Hippolyte Dumont, his father-in-law, established the ''Carrières et Fours à Chaux Dumont-Wautier'', at [[Huy|Hermalle]] in [[Belgium]]. In 1924, Léon Lhoist founded the ''Etablissements Léon Lhoist'', a [[Lime (mineral)|lime]] and [[Calcium oxide|dolime]] (dolomitic lime, or burnt [[dolomite]]) producer, at [[Rochefort, Belgium|Jemelle]], Belgium. In 1926, [[:fr:Lhoist|Lhoist]] established the ''Carrières et Fours à Chaux de Dugny'', in [[France]].

