{{italic title}}{{primary sources|date=January 2018}} {{about|the Canadian television program which aired from 2016 to 2018 on CBC News Network|other television programs with the same name|On the Money (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox television Rehmanova fatime12 | image = | image_upright = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | presenter = [[Peter Armstrong (journalist)|Peter Armstrong]] | country = Canada | language = English | producer = | news_editor = <!-- Content editor or editors of a current affairs/political show such as Newsnight. --> | runtime = <!-- Reliable source required --> | network = [[CBC News Network]] | picture_format = | first_aired = {{Start date|2016|09|12}} | last_aired = {{End date|2018|06|28}}<ref name="g+m cancel" /> | website = http://www.cbc.ca/news/onthemoney | production_website = }}
'''''On the Money''''' is a [[business journalism|business and economics news]] program which aired on [[CBC News Network]] from September 12, 2016 to June 28, 2018. Developed as a replacement for the network's previous business news program, ''[[The Exchange (TV series)|The Exchange]]'', the program was hosted by [[Peter Armstrong (journalist)|Peter Armstrong]] and aired weekdays at 4pm ET/ 1pm PT.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/mediacentre/program/on-the-money|title=On The Money - CBC Media Centre|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en}}</ref>
The program was cancelled on June 20, 2018 due to budget constraints at the CBC.<ref name="g+m cancel">{{cite news |last1=Houpt |first1=Simon |title=CBC cancels On the Money business show, cites lack of funds |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-cbc-cancels-on-the-money-business-show-cites-lack-of-funds/ |accessdate=July 5, 2018 |work=The Globe and Mail |date=June 20, 2018}}</ref>
